CSS -Cascading Stlylesheets

selector
declaration block => property-value pairs

p {
    property: value;
    property: value;
    property: values    
}

property -what you want to Stlylesheets
value - what you want to Style

p {
    color: blue;
    font: 20px
}

Selector => way of targeting html elements to style

1. universal selector (*) -elements of all type
* {.....}
2. element Selector
form {....}
ul {....}
table {...}
3. id selector (#)- elements of a specific type
<img id="cover-image" src="" alt="">
#cover -image{...}

4. class Selector
<div class ="main-layout"></div>
<section class ="main-layout"></section>
.main-layout {....}

5.group selector
a,p.h1.h2,h3 {....}

margin -space outside an elements border: betweeen the border and other elements
padding -space inside an element; between the border and the elements content1. Single
margin; 10px; => all round the element

2. double
padding: 10px 15px -> top+bottom, <left>
    3. four
margin: 0 20px 10px;->top,right,right